TontoJB is published as a public proof-of-concept research repository for a
console security exploit chain. The code, documentation, payload experiments,
proxy tooling, offsets, and related materials are provided for educational,
defensive, interoperability, archival, and good-faith security-research use by
people who understand the technical and legal risks of kernel exploitation.

Use this project only on hardware, accounts, networks, and environments that
